{
  "text": "Overall, the application of Y-27632 was less successful in the SOD1 G93A mouse model than that of fasudil. Since 30 mg/kg body weight showed only significant effects on motor function, we cannot exclude that an even higher dosage would be more beneficial. It could also be that the differential inhibitory profile toward other kinases is responsible for the lack of efficacy [CITATION_1] . Thus, some of these \"off-target\" effects on other kinases by fasudil may have been even beneficial to a certain extent in this ALS model.",
